    "body": "### Problem\n\nDocs are saying:\n\n```\n'pumborder'\t\tstring\t(default \"\")\n\t\t\tglobal\n\tDefines the default border style of popupmenu windows. Same as\n\t'winborder'.\n```\n\nHowever, pumborder does not support custom borderchars.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim --clean\n:set pumborder=+,+,+,+,+,+,+,+\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe documentation clearly states that pumborder works the same as winborder, so I would expect either the documentation to be more clear, or that it works with custom borderchars\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1407+gfafc329bbd\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.0.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.2.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from source",
